may it be for you a time of desire,/PR

/PR

O God, in the abundance of your love,/PR

respond to me in truth with your help./PR

/SCN/XXOTE/XX. The /ITMah Tovu/XX prayer is composed entirely of biblical verses: Num-
bers 24:5; Psalms 5:8, 95:6 [adapted] and 69:14./PR

/PR

/SCC/XXOMMENTARY/XX. /ITMah Tovu/XX begins with a historical progression--the tents
of our earliest ancestors, then the sanctuary of the years of wandering in
the wilderness, then the Temple in Jerusalem. Each of these is linked to
the synagogue, for it too is "your house." And I, the contemporary soul,
seeking the right moment to encounter the divine there, am thus not
alone. I am a link in the chain of tradition bearing the truth of your
salvation.    /SC/XXD.A.T./XX/PR

