ךב ר / Morning I will seek you. The /ITShah/±arit/XX service, as its name
implies, was originally meant to be recited at dawn. Our tradition views
the two daily times of change of light as sacred hours to be appreciated
with prayer and inner quiet. Though our morning service usually begins
long after sunrise, we should try to preserve something of that special
memory of dawnòs quiet blessing as we begin our prayer.    /SC/XXA.G./XX/PR

/PR

